    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/french-onion-and-lean-beef-pho/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pot with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and cook, covered, stirring occasionally, for 15 min or until they have softened and started to colour</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/french-onion-and-lean-beef-pho/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Trim and chop your <strong>spring onion[s] </strong>in half, then cut lengthways into thin strips</p><p>Tip: Soak the spring onion strips in ice cold water and they will curl up!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/french-onion-and-lean-beef-pho/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onions are starting to soften, transfer 1 tbsp per person of <strong>softened onion</strong> to a bowl and set aside for a garnish</p><p>Add your <strong>ketjap manis </strong>and <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>to the pot and cook, uncovered, for 3-4 min or until sticky and caramelised</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/french-onion-and-lean-beef-pho/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion is sticky and caramelised, add your <strong>mince </strong>with your <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>and cook for<strong> </strong>3-4 min, breaking it up with a wooden spoon until slightly browned</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/french-onion-and-lean-beef-pho/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once slightly browned, add 850ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[1.1L]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.5L] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>with your <strong>pho broth paste</strong>, <strong>beef stock mix </strong>and <strong>soy sauce </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/french-onion-and-lean-beef-pho/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, add your <strong>rice noodles</strong> cook for 6-7 min or until cooked with a slight bite and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>french onion pho</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/french-onion-and-lean-beef-pho/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>french onion pho </strong>in a bowl</p><p>Spoon the <strong>reserved softened onions </strong>into the centre and garnish with the <strong>drained spring onion curls</strong></p><p>Finish with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
